HEADWORD: Incertitude
<hw>In*cer"ti*tude</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>incertitude</ets>, LL. <ets>incertitudo</ets>, fr. L.
<ets>incertus</ets>. See <er>Incertain</er>.]</ety> <def>Uncertainty;
doubtfulness; doubt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>incertitude</qex> and instability of this life.</q>
<rj><qau>Holland.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He fails . . . from mere <qex>incertitude</qex> or
irresolution.</q> <rj><qau>I. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incertum</ent>⟦br⟧
